FBIS4-14339 "drnes083_s_94005" FBIS-NES-94-083 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 Iran Ministry Official Comments Ministry Official Comments LD2804212694 Tehran IRNA in English 2106 GMT 28 Apr 94 LD2804212694 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Tehran, April 28, IRNA -- The Foreign Ministry today summoned the British charge d'affaires here, Geoffrey James over the allegations by British officials and media of collaboration between Iranian security officials and the Irish Republican Army (IRA). Foreign Ministry Director General for West European Affairs, 'Ali Ahani, told IRNA that Iran strongly denied the claim and dismissed it as "utterly false". "We categorically reject reports of collaboration between Iranian security officials and IRA and regard such allegations as totally groundless," he said. Ahani expressed regret the malicious propaganda of the British media.
